il all gnocchi is cooked. Serve immediately."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Serve gnocchi with pan-fried butter and herbs (e.g. rosemary, sage) topped with grated Parmesan cheese.","Try serving with tomato pasta sauce or Arrabbiata sauce<em>.<\/em> <em><\/em>","Form folded pillow-type gnocchi using two forks. Take a 1 - 3 cm piece of dough, place one fork on each diagonal corner and press the corners together to form 'folded' pillows. Repeat with all gnocchi.","To freeze, place uncooked gnocchi in a single layer on a floured board and place in the freezer for 3 - 4 hours. Once frozen, store in a sealed freezer bag and return to the freezer until required. Gnocchi can be cooked directly from frozen. Proceed as per recipe above from step 7."],"basicInfo":["medium","30m","1h 40m","8 portions"]}